<% provide(:title, accessed_page_name) %>

<section class="container">

    <section class="container">
        <h2>Welcome to SknService</h2>

        <%= image_tag("AccessProfile-ContentProfile.png", alt: "Main Path", class: "large-image") %>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
        <div class="panel panel-info">
            <div class="panel-body">
                <h5>Content-based Authorization Specification</h5>
                <dl class="dl-horizontal">
                    <dt>Key/Value tuple where:</dt>
                    <dd>key is a single record for each user labeled ContentProfile.</dd>
                    <dd>value is collection of associated ContentProfileEntry(s).</dd>
                    <dd>Content Profiles are indentified by an unique token assigned by the authentication service.</dd>
                    <dt>Profile: One</dt>
                    <dd>key is an unique combination of: &lt;UUID&gt;/&lt;ProfileType&gt;</dd>
                    <dd>value is collection of &lt;ProfileEntry&gt; the user shall access.</dd>
                    <dd>Each User has only one of these.</dd>
                    <dt>Profile Entry: Many</dt>
                    <dd>key is unique combination of: &lt;ContentType&gt;/&lt;EntityType&gt;/&lt;EntityTypeOpts&gt;</dd>
                    <dd>value is collection of &lt;ContentTypeOpts&gt; the user shall access.</dd>
                    <dd>Each User can have many of these.</dd>
                </dl>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section class="container">
        <div class="row">
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h2>ContentProfile</h2>
                <p>Determines if a specific user can access or interact with a specific object by type or name of object.</p>
                <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="<%= model_details_path()  %>" role="button">View details &raquo;</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h2>AccessProfile</h2>
                <p>Applies an Authorization Profile to each Authenticated User; which was created by the Administrator.  Using the roles assigned, access to navigation, and/or viewable, elements is controlled.</p>
                <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="<%= model_details_path()  %>" role="button">View details &raquo;</a></p>
            </div>
            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h2>Authentication</h2>
                <p>Every incoming has both the authentication and authorization features of this site applied.  No access returns you to login or home page.  No authorization returns you to home page.  Should you attempt a url outside what is allowed and provided for, you will directed to the home page with access still being denied.</p>
                <p><a class="btn btn-default" href="<%= model_details_path()  %>" role="button">View details &raquo;</a></p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

</section>